translated:
Gösta Wilhelm, lawyer, Ulricehamn, b. 28/2/07 in Umeå, son of the first postal assistant Wilhelm W. and Amanda Tjulin. — Studied in Umeå until 1926, graduated with a law degree in Stockholm in 1933. Traveled to France, Germany, Belgium in 1927 and Finland in 1932. Worked as a court clerk in the intermediate court of Västmanland between 1934-1936. Established his own law office, Gösta Warborg law firm, in Ulricehamn from 1937. Hobbies: music, composition. 
Tage Wilhelm Birger, manager, Varberg, b. 18/4/14 in Varberg, son of the factory worker Birger Svensson and Alida Skulander. Married in 1940 to Britt Sjögren. Children: Sten b. 1942, Britt-Marie b. 1944, Bengt b. 1945. Works as a manager and chairman of the board in A-B Cykelfabrik Monark and A-B Värnamo Gummi factory.
